llotment of calories. She describes how surplus food is produced and distributed, and she considers both the motives for the generous sharing she has observed among the Dobe !Kung and some evolutionary implications of that behavior.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0a!Kung (African people)xAnthropometry. 0a!Kung (African people)xFood. 0a!Kung (African people)xHealth and hygiene. 0a!Kung (African people)xNutrition. 0aBody sizezKalahari Desert. 0aFood habitszKalahari Desert. 0aFoodxCaloric contentzKalahari Desert. 0aHunting and gathering societieszKalahari Desert. 0aLife cycle, Human. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Physical.2bisacsh  aanthropological data set.  aanthropology.  abiographical.  abushmen.  acultural anthropology.  adiscussion books.  adobe kung.  aethnographers.  aevolutionary implications.  afood.  agenerational.  agood health.  aharsh environment.  ahuman behavior.  ahuman culture.  ahunter gatherers.  akalahari desert.  alife analysis.  alife histories.  alife spans.  alife stages.  alow calorie diets.  anonfiction.  aphysical anthropology.  aremote places.  aretrospective.  ascientists.  asharing culture.  asociology anthropology.  aweight issues.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094617040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520946170423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520946170/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles